title: Travel spending of U.S. travelers by age group 2015
summary: This is a multi-line chart with 8 lines representing Less than 1,000 U.S. dollars, 1,000-3,999 U.S. dollars, 4,000-3,000 U.S. dollars, 8,000-11,999 U.S. dollars, 12,000-15,999 U.S. dollars, 16,000-19,999 U.S. dollars, 20,000-24,999 U.S. dollars, and 25,000 U.S. dollars or more. The y axis denotes Share of respondents and the x axis denotes Year.

Overall Less than 1,000 U.S. dollars, and 8,000-11,999 U.S. dollars are gradually increasing, 1,000-3,999 U.S. dollars, and 16,000-19,999 U.S. dollars are gradually decreasing, 4,000-3,000 U.S. dollars, 12,000-15,999 U.S. dollars, 20,000-24,999 U.S. dollars, and 25,000 U.S. dollars or more are roughly constant,  throughout the Year

Throughout the period, 1,000-3,999 U.S. dollars generally had the highest Share of respondents relative to others with an average of 37.33, and it reached its maximum at 21-34_years_old with a value of 43.0.
After 1,000-3,999 U.S. dollars, 4,000-3,000 U.S. dollars overall has the second highest values , with a mean value of 21.0, peaking at 35-54_years_old.
20,000-24,999 U.S. dollars mostly had the least Share of respondents with a mean value of 2.67, which peaked at 21-34_years_old, and 35-54_years_old with a value of 3.0.
